2014). Practitioners are supported to develop their practice by exploring new research and innovative ways of working within the field, while promoting the importance of learning from experience and building resilience in adult safeguarding work. This book includes: • helpful case studies and examples of professional decision making from experienced adult safeguarding practitioners; • top tips and models to enable confident application of knowledge to practice; • tools for reflection to extend the practitioner’s development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aOlder peoplexAbuse ofzGreat BritainxPrevention. 0aOlder peoplexCarezGreat Britain. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxAbuse ofzGreat BritainxPrevention. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxCarezGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aHubbard, Rachel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311119671840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447351702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447351702/original  a978-3-11-119671-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles